The Hindus in arunachal are non-northeasterns, living temporarily in the state. that's what I meant by "non-native". This is also called floating population. In 2020-their population dropped to about 3%. They cannot be classified under the "Demographics" of native northeastern. Reference: http://14.139.206.50:8080/jspui/bitstream/1/341/1/RELIGIOUS%20HISTORY%20OF%20ARUNACHAL%20PRADESH.pdf
Bodo, Garo, Dimasa, etc are Koch-Kacharis. We need a Kachari page for the entire community, similar to the Naga/Tai/Tani pages.
Lepcha comes under Sikkimese people. Yes they are lepchas in other states of NE, but this page is for the whole northeast.
This page is about the entire northeast. Bengalis are a minority
Improved the Demographic Page. This page repeated the same ethnicities over and over again, by different names- that refer to the same community
Kuki-Zo is not a minority community. Was mentioned in the Majority community already

Tamang, Rai, Limbu comes under Gorkha. Was redundant. They are collectively not a minority community.
